he move in April.<br>Tuesday I stopped by and she was a little tired, but still doing very well.<br>My sister called her on Wednesday and said she seemed a little weird...even forgot who she was, but when I talked to her Wednesday night she seemed on the ball.  Everyone says I should reward coharent behavior with comapny so I asked if she wanted to go to dinner Thursday night.  She was really excited.<br>Thursday she seemed a little slow, but other wise good.  We went to a buffet and she was able to move around, get her own food, follow conversations, and not make a fool of herself (ei...falling aleep at the table like she did at Burger King that one time).<br>She fell asleep on the way home (but at least she didn't try to open the door on the freeway again...) and woke up as soon as we stopped.<br>This morning she called me and asked if I would take her to the pharmacy to get a script.  I said ok.<br>When I got there to pick her up she was just hanging up the phone from calling a restaraunt next to the pharmacy and lunch would be ready to pick up too.<br>She went in the pharmacy and I ran into the 99cent store next door.<br>Everything went well and I dropped her back at home and went to work.<br><br>Ed called at 7:30 and said that he got home to find the house dark and she was laying on the living room floor unconscious.  He said it looked like someone beat the shit out of her.<br>It wasn't a break-in type thing...she has two huge dogs that have free roam of the house and they are very mean to strangers.<br>I went straight over (she lves 5 mins from me) and sure enough she has two black eyes, a busted lip, and her face is so swollen she can't open her eyes.  She was still passed out and she had wet herself.<br><br>Ed called the pharmacy to find out what she picked up...then we proceeded to count pills.<br>She took 1 of the med she was supossed to take 4 of, and 4 of the med she was supposed to take 1 of.<br>She took 4 anti depressants and cause severe drowsiness.<br><br>I don't think this was a deliberate act to get high...I think it was an honest to god accident.<br>We won't know anything until she wakes up.<br> <p><a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/bachesandpains>The Support Lounge</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor= CCCCFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/ulisainfl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisa in fl </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/smileys/coffee.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mrs. Fix-it!</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#000000>(2/9/02 4:05:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/images/puppies2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My Mom</span><hr size=1> OMG! Keep us posted, Kitty Kitty. <p>  <center><img src="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/misc./schi-k11.gif"></a><P><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/banimalfriends"><img src="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/images/fb.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor= CCCCFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/udonleeann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DonLeeAnn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/religion/angeleyz_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Friendly Shoulder</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#000000>(2/9/02 5:28:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gifs.net/an